But they did accomplish one thing that will have far-reaching implications for young daredevils: passing a law requiring that children under 14 wear safety helmets while riding skateboards in public areas.
The measure, which Gov.
George E. Pataki signed on Nov. 16, mirrors the state laws already in place to protect bicycle riders and those who use in-line skates against serious head injuries.
"Skateboards can be at least as dangerous to ride as bicycles or in-line skates," according to a legislative memorandum in support of the bill.
